summary: This code imports necessary libraries, makes an HTTP POST request to "http://localhost:8786/post" with data containing a key-value pair and another key-value pair of "key2" and "value2". The successful response is handled by printing the sent data using the message function. Additionally, it sets `cnds` as formatted company candidates and sends this along with "key2" in the POST request.

details.comment: This code imports necessary libraries, makes an HTTP POST request to "http://localhost:8786/post" with data containing a key-value pair and another key-value pair of "key2" and "value2". The successful response is handled by printing the sent data using the message function. Additionally, it sets `cnds` as formatted company candidates and sends this along with "key2" in the POST request.
details.content:
(require 'package)
(package-initialize)
(require 'request)
(request "http://localhost:8786/post" 
	 :type "POST" 
	 :data '(("key" . "value") ("key2" . "value2")) 
	 :parser 'json-read 
	 :success (cl-function(lambda (&key data &allow-other-keys)
	(message "I sent: %S" (assoc-default 'form data)))))
(require 'company)
(find-file "lsp.sh")
(company-mode)
(company-complete-common)
(setq cnds (format "%s" company-candidates))
(request "http://localhost:8786/post" :type "POST" :data `(("key" . ,cnds) ("key2" . "value2")) :parser 'json-read :success (cl-function(lambda (&key data &allow-other-keys)(message "I sent: %S" (assoc-default 'form data)))))
